FLORENCE, S.C. -- The Drs. Bruce and Lee Foundation Library in Florence will show a super hero movie Tuesday night.
Black Panther, which stars Chadwick Boseman, Michael B. Jordan, Lupita Nyongâ€™o, Danai Gurira, Martin Freeman, Daniel Kaluuya, Letitia Wright, Winston Duke, Angela Bassett, Forest Whitaker, and Andy Serkis, is the first Marvel film with a presdominantly black cast.
Black Panther runs 2:15 and is raged PG-13.
Admission is free and light refreshments will be served.
The Doctors Bruce and Lee Foundation Library is located at 509 S. Dargan Street in Florence. For additional information or to register call 843-413-7074. The film is sponsored by Friends of Florence County Library.
